candidates.title: Maintenance, dependency updates
candidates.body:
Updates a bunch of rust dependencies, removing 6 security vulnerabilities (cargo audit)

Some lingering TODO's:
- rewrite qsync to use the most recent syn version
- update the storage plugin to use the more recent AWS crates
- update the docs site to use the more recent docusaurus versions

candidates.title: Add rudementry email template support, available with the auth plugin
candidates.body:
Fixes #75 
Addresses #37 

example usage:

to use the default templates, but with a custom base_url,
```rust
let app_data = create_rust_app::setup()
    .with_custom_email_templates(DefaultMailTemplates::new("https://your.url.com/");
```

to use your own templates, create a struct that implements the `EmailTemplates` trait, and pass an instance of it to the `with_custom_email_templates` function as before

candidates.title: Ci fixes
candidates.body:
make the cli CI routines create a schema.rs that is usable for testing, bypassing the need for diesel in testing and allowing CI to pass

also fixes a few clippy lints

* Fixes compilation issues :rocket: (#140)
* View dev-hosted app outside the network (for example, now you can view the local app on your phone!)
* `qsync` updates
* Updated service boilerplate generation (#102)
* Other minor issues including #168

candidates.title: Ci improvements
candidates.body:
fixes #103 

includes a much improved CI pipeline that generates projects with various parameters and tries to compile them (test succeeds if compilation succeeds)

also removes references to the dev plugin from the CLI (see: #141 )

also fixes some clippy warnings from a few previous commits

0.10.2

Upgrade notes

  • MSRV is now 1.60 (#828)

Features

  • Allow providing a custom tokio stream for AsyncSmtpTransport (#805)

Bug fixes

Misc

missing: an example of adding Docs to a end-users endpoints, documentation skeleton in generated services (and necessary traits on generated models) (these 2 will need to be done in a PR for Dsync), apidocs for poem backend, an example `ApiDoc` structure, etc.

candidates.body:
I've had this stashed for a while, finally ended up testing it tonight and it looks like it's ready to go. I'll list the changes this brings shortly.

* #64 fixes dependency issues
* #57 migration files
* #53 (related PR: #65): switched to using tsync as a library which should partly fix the errors we're seeing here on windows
* #52 wasn't entirely fixed, but I've added a test to make sure projects aren't generated which have the dev but not the auth plugin enabled

* Integrated [dsync](https://github.com/Wulf/dsync)
* Fixed the starter template a bit

candidates.title: Bundle sqlite
candidates.body: ~Allow bundling~ bundle the sqlite3 library, rather than relying on dynamic linking to a system sqlite3 library, which may be out-of-date or nonexistent.

candidates.title: replace `argonautica` with `rust-argon2`
candidates.body: `argonautica` seems to be unmaintained for 3 years now and only supports the C-implementation. `rust-argon2` seems to be the go-to modern pure-rust implementation, so I tried to replace it bit for bit as well as I could.
